OL,3,CHealth risks of climate change reach
OL,4,Crecord breaking levels, experts warn
OL,6,FThe higher frequency of heatwaves and
OL,7,Fdroughts was linked to 151 million
OL,8,Fmore people experiencing moderate or
OL,9,Fsevere food insecurity than they were
OL,10,Feach year between 1981 and 2010.
OL,12,FAt the same time, 61% of the world's
OL,13,Fland area saw an increase in extreme
OL,14,Frainstorms in the past decade,
OL,15,Fincreasing the risk of flooding,
OL,16,Finfectious disease and water
OL,17,Fcontamination, while the risk of
OL,18,Fmosquito-borne diseases such as dengue
OL,19,Fhas increased.
