OL,3,CHealth risks of climate change reach
OL,4,Crecord breaking levels, experts warn
OL,6,F"No individual or economy on the
OL,7,Fplanet is immune from the health
OL,8,Fthreats of climate change.
OL,10,F"The relentless expansion of fossil
OL,11,Ffuels and record-breaking greenhouse
OL,12,Fgas emissions compounds these
OL,13,Fdangerous health impacts, and is
OL,14,Fthreatening to reverse the limited
OL,15,Fprogress made so far, and put a
OL,16,Fhealthy future further out of reach."
OL,18,FDr Romanello added: "Despite this
OL,19,Fthreat, we see financial resources
OL,20,Fcontinue to be invested in the very
OL,21,Fthings that undermine our health.
